Li Wins First Set Against Schiavone 6-4 in the French Open Women’s Final

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-06-04T13:51:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-04/li-wins-first-set-against-schiavone-6-4-in-the-french-open-women-s-final.html
Li Na  took the first set against
defending champion Francesca Schiavone 6-4 in the French Open
women’s tennis final.  Li is attempting to become the first Chinese player to win
a Grand Slam singles title. She lost the Australian Open final
in January to  Kim Clijsters .  Schiavone is seeking to become the sixth woman to defend
her French Open title since tennis turned professional in 1968.
 Belgium ’s Justine Henin was the last in 2007.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  